'''Kelly Brannigan''' (born [[September 18]], [[1982]] in [[Torrance, California]], U.S.A.<ref name='NBC â "Deal" â Kelly Brannigan'>{{cite web|title="Deal or No Deal" â Kelly Brannigan bio|url=http://www.nbc.com/Deal_or_No_Deal/models/kelly.shtml|publisher=NBC|accessdate=25 September 2011}}</ref>) is an [[United States|American]] [[Model (person)|model]]. She is best known as the model holding case #24 on the hit U.S. game show [[Deal or No Deal (U.S. game show)|''Deal or No Deal'']] from 2006 to 2009.<ref name='NBC â "Deal" â Kelly Brannigan' />
== Early life ==
Brannigan spent her early childhood in southern California.<ref name='NBC â "Deal" â Kelly Brannigan' /> She moved to [[Auburn, New York]], after the death of her father, Mark, in 1993.<ref name='NBC â "Deal" â Kelly Brannigan' />
She is a 2000 graduate of [[Auburn High School (New York)|Auburn High School]].<ref name="The Citizen â Oct. 2006">{{cite news|last=Wilcox|first=David|title=She thrives to be No. 1|url=http://auburnpub.com/lifestyles/article_d7b46154-2fc6-5491-b8a7-fdf36c75e46a.html|accessdate=25 September 2011|newspaper=The Citizen (Auburn, New York)|date=23 October 2006}}</ref> She earned an [[associate's degree]] in [[hotel management]] from [[Monroe Community College]] in [[Rochester, New York]], and also studied at the [[Culinary Institute of America]].<ref name="The Citizen â Oct. 2006" />
== Career == Brannigan returned to her native southern California in 2006 to pursue a career in [[Model (person)|modeling]].<ref name="The Citizen â Oct. 2006" /> Less than a year later, she was hired by the prime-time TV game show [[Deal or No Deal (U.S. game show)|''Deal or No Deal'']] to replace [[Meghan Markle]] as the model holding case #24.<ref name='NBC â "Deal" â Kelly Brannigan' /> Brannigan remained on the show, which was hosted by [[Howie Mandel]] and aired on [[NBC]], until its cancellation in 2009.<ref name='NBC â "Deal" â Kelly Brannigan' />
Brannigan has appeared on TV shows including ''[[CSI: Miami]]'', ''[[Entourage (TV series)|Entourage]]'', and ''[[My Fair Brady]]''.
Brannigan has appeared in national [[TV commercial]]s, including a [http://sevenfan.blogspot.com/2010/02/matthew-staffords-axe-hair-action.html 2010 AXE Hair ad] featuring [[NFL]] quarterback [[Matthew Stafford]].
Brannigan was the "Lovely Lady of the Day" at [[SI.com|SportsIllustrated.com]] on July 8, 2011.<ref name="SI.com â Hot Clicks">{{cite news|last=Traina|first=Jimmy|title=Hot Clicks|url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2011/extramustard/hotclicks/07/08/kelly-brannigan-derek-jeters-top-pop-culture-moments/index.html|accessdate=25 September 2011|publisher=SI.com|date=8 July 2011}}</ref>
